rComments: I found her to be very unclear and would ramble in lectures. Plus, her grading was very tough and she seemed pretty unavailable most of the time when students needed help. She rarely replied to e-mails within a reasonable time (it usually took her more than a couple of days). I probably wouldn't take another class with her.

She's a tough grader. However, grading criteria are always clear, and feedback after grading makes you realize that the grade you received was justified. If anything, knowing that she is a tough grader pushed me to work harder and double check everything I handed in. Also, she was ALWAYS there to help out and answer questions about assignments.
Extremely high expectations. Lectures aren't very clear. Gives little feedback on work and appeared uninterested in helping her students.
